The department&#8217;s Jessica Shelver says officials have been able to accommodate most of the learners. CAPE TOWN The Western Cape Education Department says there are still about 2,600 learners who are yet to be placed at schools in the province.When the new school year started initially, 18,500 children couldn t be placed. But the department s Jessica Shelver says officials have been able to accommodate most of the learners. This represents 0,04% of our total learner population. The demand is mainly concentrated in the urban metro areas and the challenges that we ve experienced this term are late enrollment and persons that are relocating to the Western Cape. 